{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":440,"text":"The word concussion evokes a fear\nthese days more so than it ever has,"},{"time":5120,"text":"and I know this personally."},{"time":7520,"text":"I played 10 years of football,"},{"time":10200,"text":"was struck in the head thousands of times."},{"time":12640,"text":"And I have to tell you, though,\nwhat was much worse than that"},{"time":16320,"text":"was a pair of bike accidents I had\nwhere I suffered concussions,"},{"time":21120,"text":"and I'm still dealing with the effects\nof the most recent one"},{"time":24080,"text":"today as I stand in front of you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27640,"text":"There is a fear around concussion"},{"time":30120,"text":"that does have some evidence behind it."},{"time":33600,"text":"There is information\nthat a repeated history of concussion"},{"time":36960,"text":"can lead to early dementia,\nsuch as Alzheimer's,"},{"time":40280,"text":"and chronic traumatic encephalopathy."},{"time":42360,"text":"That was the subject\nof the Will Smith movie \"Concussion.\""},{"time":46560,"text":"And so everybody is caught up in football\nand what they see in the military,"},{"time":50160,"text":"but you may not know"},{"time":51520,"text":"that bike riding is the leading cause\nof concussion for kids,"},{"time":55840,"text":"sports-related concussion, that is."},{"time":59040,"text":"And so another thing\nthat I should tell you"},{"time":61640,"text":"that you may not know"},{"time":62880,"text":"is that the helmets that are worn\nin bicycling and football"},{"time":65840,"text":"and many activities,"},{"time":67520,"text":"they're not designed or tested"},{"time":70120,"text":"for how well they can protect\nyour children against concussion."},{"time":74200,"text":"They're in fact designed and tested"},{"time":75960,"text":"for their ability to protect\nagainst skull fracture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79840,"text":"And so I get this question\nall the time from parents,"},{"time":85480,"text":"and they ask me,"},{"time":87080,"text":"\"Would you let your own child\nplay football?\""},{"time":89400,"text":"Or, \"Should I let my child play soccer?\""},{"time":92600,"text":"And I think that as a field,"},{"time":95520,"text":"we're a long way from giving an answer\nwith any kind of confidence there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101440,"text":"So I look at that question\nfrom a bit of a different lens,"},{"time":105040,"text":"and I want to know,\nhow can we prevent concussion?"},{"time":108800,"text":"Is that even possible?"},{"time":110480,"text":"And most experts think that it's not,"},{"time":114520,"text":"but the work that we're doing in my lab"},{"time":116760,"text":"is starting to reveal more\nof the details around concussion"},{"time":121160,"text":"so that we can have\na better understanding."},{"time":123960,"text":"The reason we're able\nto prevent skull fracture with helmets"},{"time":126840,"text":"is because it's pretty simple.\nWe know how it works."},{"time":129320,"text":"Concussion has been\nmuch more of a mystery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132280,"text":"So to give you a sense of what might\nbe happening in a concussion,"},{"time":137240,"text":"I want to show you the video here"},{"time":139200,"text":"that you see when you type into Google,"},{"time":141760,"text":"\"What is a concussion?\""},{"time":143200,"text":"The CDC website comes up,"},{"time":144880,"text":"and this video essentially\ntells the whole story."},{"time":148360,"text":"What you see is the head moves forward,"},{"time":150800,"text":"the brain lags behind,"},{"time":152880,"text":"then the brain catches up"},{"time":154320,"text":"and smashes into the skull."},{"time":156600,"text":"It rebounds off the skull"},{"time":158800,"text":"and then proceeds to run\ninto the other side of the skull."},{"time":163320,"text":"And what you'll notice is highlighted\nin this video from the CDC,"},{"time":166960,"text":"which I'll note was funded by the NFL,"},{"time":169440,"text":"is that the outer surface of the brain,"},{"time":172400,"text":"where it was to have\nsmashed into the skull,"},{"time":175720,"text":"looks like it's been damaged or injured,\nso it's on the outer surface of the brain."},{"time":179680,"text":"And what I'd like to do with this video"},{"time":181680,"text":"is to tell you that there are\nsome aspects that are probably right,"},{"time":185400,"text":"indicative of what the scientists\nthink happens with concussion,"},{"time":188440,"text":"but there's probably more\nthat's wrong with this video."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191080,"text":"So one thing that I do agree with,\nand I think most experts would,"},{"time":194360,"text":"is that the brain\ndoes have these dynamics."},{"time":196400,"text":"It does lag behind the skull"},{"time":198800,"text":"and then catch up and move\nback and forth and oscillate."},{"time":201480,"text":"That we think is true."},{"time":203760,"text":"However, the amount of motion\nyou see in the brain in this video"},{"time":207080,"text":"is probably not right at all."},{"time":208680,"text":"There's very little room\nin the cranial vault,"},{"time":212120,"text":"only a few millimeters,"},{"time":213840,"text":"and it's filled entirely\nwith cerebral spinal fluid,"},{"time":217040,"text":"which acts as a protective layer."},{"time":219240,"text":"And so the brain as a whole probably\nmoves very little inside the skull."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224520,"text":"The other problem with this video"},{"time":226600,"text":"is that the brain is shown"},{"time":228360,"text":"as a kind of rigid whole\nas it moves around,"},{"time":231480,"text":"and that's not true either."},{"time":233720,"text":"Your brain is one of the softest\nsubstances in your body,"},{"time":237160,"text":"and you can think of it\nkind of like jello."},{"time":239200,"text":"So as your head is moving back and forth,"},{"time":241360,"text":"your brain is twisting\nand turning and contorting,"},{"time":244240,"text":"and the tissue is getting stretched."},{"time":246480,"text":"And so most experts, I think, would agree"},{"time":249520,"text":"that concussion is not likely\nto be something that's happening"},{"time":252680,"text":"on this outer surface of the brain,"},{"time":254520,"text":"but rather it's something\nthat's much deeper"},{"time":256640,"text":"towards the center of the brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259279,"text":"Now, the way that we're\napproaching this problem"},{"time":261880,"text":"to try to understand\nthe mechanisms of concussion"},{"time":264240,"text":"and to figure out if we can prevent it"},{"time":266120,"text":"is we are using a device like this."},{"time":268960,"text":"It's a mouthguard."},{"time":270960,"text":"It has sensors in it\nthat are essentially the same"},{"time":273880,"text":"that are in your cell phone:"},{"time":275240,"text":"accelerometers, gyroscopes,"},{"time":277600,"text":"and when someone is struck in the head,"},{"time":279520,"text":"it can tell you how their head moved"},{"time":282080,"text":"at a thousand samples per second."},{"time":286760,"text":"The principle behind\nthe mouthguard is this:"},{"time":289480,"text":"it fits onto your teeth."},{"time":290760,"text":"Your teeth are one of the hardest\nsubstances in your body."},{"time":293840,"text":"So it rigidly couples to your skull"},{"time":295920,"text":"and gives you the most precise\npossible measurement"},{"time":298360,"text":"of how the skull moves."},{"time":300320,"text":"People have tried\nother approaches, with helmets."},{"time":302880,"text":"We've looked at other sensors\nthat go on your skin,"},{"time":306280,"text":"and they all simply move around too much,"},{"time":308920,"text":"and so we found that this\nis the only reliable way"},{"time":311640,"text":"to take a good measurement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315400,"text":"So now that we've got this device,\nwe can go beyond studying cadavers,"},{"time":319720,"text":"because you can only\nlearn so much about concussion"},{"time":322160,"text":"from studying a cadaver,"},{"time":323400,"text":"and we want to learn\nand study live humans."},{"time":326200,"text":"So where can we find\na group of willing volunteers"},{"time":330120,"text":"to go out and smash their heads\ninto each other on a regular basis"},{"time":334400,"text":"and sustain concussion?"},{"time":335640,"text":"Well, I was one of them,"},{"time":337560,"text":"and it's your local friendly\nStanford football team."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341640,"text":"So this is our laboratory,"},{"time":343280,"text":"and I want to show you"},{"time":345000,"text":"the first concussion\nwe measured with this device."},{"time":348200,"text":"One of the things that I should point out\nis the device has this gyroscope in it,"},{"time":352480,"text":"and that allows you\nto measure the rotation of the head."},{"time":355240,"text":"Most experts think\nthat that's the critical factor"},{"time":357640,"text":"that might start to tell us\nwhat is happening in concussion."},{"time":360520,"text":"So please watch this video."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363280,"text":"Announcer: Cougars bring\nextra people late, but Luck has time,"},{"time":366720,"text":"and Winslow is crushed."},{"time":370120,"text":"I hope he's all right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":371720,"text":"(Audience roars)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":378560,"text":"Top of your screen,"},{"time":380040,"text":"you'll see him come on\njust this little post route,"},{"time":382480,"text":"get separation, safety."},{"time":388240,"text":"Here it comes at you in real speed.\nYou'll hear this."},{"time":392640,"text":"The hit delivered by --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":395720,"text":"David Camarillo: Sorry, three times\nis probably a little excessive there."},{"time":399200,"text":"But you get the idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":400480,"text":"So when you look at just the film here,"},{"time":403320,"text":"pretty much the only thing you can see\nis he got hit really hard and he was hurt."},{"time":407160,"text":"But when we extract the data"},{"time":408840,"text":"out of the mouthguard that he was wearing,"},{"time":410864,"text":"we can see much more detail,\nmuch richer information."},{"time":413600,"text":"And one of the things that we noticed here"},{"time":416040,"text":"is that he was struck\nin the lower left side of his face mask."},{"time":420120,"text":"And so that did something first\nthat was a little counterintuitive."},{"time":423320,"text":"His head did not move to the right."},{"time":425040,"text":"In fact, it rotated first to the left."},{"time":427000,"text":"Then as the neck began to compress,"},{"time":429880,"text":"the force of the blow caused it\nto whip back to the right."},{"time":433000,"text":"So this left-right motion\nwas sort of a whiplash-type phenomenon,"},{"time":438880,"text":"and we think that is probably\nwhat led to the brain injury."}]},{"cues":[{"time":443320,"text":"Now, this device is only limited in such\nthat it can measure the skull motion,"},{"time":447120,"text":"but what we really want to know\nis what's happening inside of the brain."},{"time":450560,"text":"So we collaborate with\nSvein Kleiven's group in Sweden."},{"time":454080,"text":"They've developed a finite element\nmodel of the brain."},{"time":457680,"text":"And so this is a simulation"},{"time":459800,"text":"using the data from our mouthguard\nfrom the injury I just showed you,"},{"time":463160,"text":"and what you see is the brain --"},{"time":465200,"text":"this is a cross-section right in the front"},{"time":467640,"text":"of the brain twisting\nand contorting as I mentioned."},{"time":470440,"text":"So you can see this doesn't\nlook a lot like the CDC video."},{"time":473360,"text":"Now, the colors that you're looking at"},{"time":475240,"text":"are how much the brain tissue\nis being stretched."},{"time":479400,"text":"And so the red is 50 percent."},{"time":481120,"text":"That means the brain has been stretched\nto 50 percent of its original length,"},{"time":484800,"text":"the tissue in that particular area."}]},{"cues":[{"time":486520,"text":"And the main thing I want to draw\nyour attention to is this red spot."},{"time":489800,"text":"So the red spot is very close\nto the center of the brain,"},{"time":493280,"text":"and relatively speaking,"},{"time":494560,"text":"you don't see a lot of colors like that\non the exterior surface"},{"time":499240,"text":"as the CDC video showed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":502960,"text":"Now, to explain a little more detail"},{"time":504720,"text":"about how we think\nconcussion might be happening,"},{"time":508360,"text":"one thing I should mention"},{"time":509680,"text":"is that we and others have observed\nthat a concussion is more likely"},{"time":512919,"text":"when you're struck and your head\nrotates in this direction."},{"time":516919,"text":"This is more common\nin sports like football,"},{"time":519200,"text":"but this seems to be more dangerous.\nSo what might be happening there?"},{"time":522559,"text":"Well, one thing that you'll notice\nin the human brain"},{"time":525600,"text":"that is different than other animals"},{"time":527360,"text":"is we have these two very large lobes."},{"time":529840,"text":"We have the right brain\nand the left brain."},{"time":532080,"text":"And the key thing\nto notice in this figure here"},{"time":535160,"text":"is that right down the center\nof the right brain and the left brain"},{"time":538440,"text":"there's a large fissure\nthat goes deep into the brain."},{"time":541400,"text":"And in that fissure,\nwhat you can't see in this image,"},{"time":544280,"text":"you'll have to trust me,"},{"time":545520,"text":"there is a fibrous sheet of tissue."},{"time":547240,"text":"It's called the falx,"},{"time":548480,"text":"and it runs from the front of your head\nall the way to the back of your head,"},{"time":552160,"text":"and it's quite stiff."},{"time":553400,"text":"And so what that allows for\nis when you're struck"},{"time":556880,"text":"and your head rotates\nin this left-right direction,"},{"time":559960,"text":"forces can rapidly transmit\nright down to the center of your brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":563760,"text":"Now, what's there\nat the bottom of this fissure?"},{"time":567120,"text":"It's the wiring of your brain,"},{"time":569640,"text":"and in fact this red bundle\nhere at the bottom of that fissure"},{"time":574280,"text":"is the single largest fiber bundle"},{"time":577280,"text":"that is the wiring that connects\nthe right and left sides of your brain."},{"time":581280,"text":"It's called the corpus callosum."},{"time":583480,"text":"And we think that this might be"},{"time":585440,"text":"one of the most common\nmechanisms of concussion,"},{"time":589280,"text":"and as the forces move down,\nthey strike the corpus callosum,"},{"time":594000,"text":"it causes a dissociation\nbetween your right and your left brain"},{"time":597000,"text":"and could explain some\nof the symptoms of concussion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":600680,"text":"This finding is also consistent\nof what we've seen"},{"time":603520,"text":"in this brain disease that I mentioned,\nchronic traumatic encephalopathy."},{"time":607560,"text":"So this is an image of a middle-aged\nex-professional football player,"},{"time":613120,"text":"and the thing that I want to point out\nis if you look at the corpus callosum,"},{"time":617120,"text":"and I'll page back here so you can see\nthe size of a normal corpus callosum"},{"time":621080,"text":"and the size of the person here\nwho has chronic traumatic encephalopathy,"},{"time":625520,"text":"it is greatly atrophied."},{"time":628080,"text":"And the same goes\nfor all of the space in the ventricles."},{"time":631440,"text":"These ventricles are much larger."},{"time":633240,"text":"And so all of this tissue\nnear the center of the brain"},{"time":635800,"text":"has died off over time."},{"time":637040,"text":"So what we're learning\nis indeed consistent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":641520,"text":"Now, there is some good news here,"},{"time":644200,"text":"and I hope to give you a sense\nof hope by the end of this talk."},{"time":647680,"text":"One of the things that we've noticed,"},{"time":649800,"text":"specifically about\nthis mechanism of injury,"},{"time":652080,"text":"is although there's a rapid transmission\nof the forces down this fissure,"},{"time":656160,"text":"it still takes a defined amount of time."},{"time":659480,"text":"And what we think is that if we can\nslow the head down just enough"},{"time":663840,"text":"so that the brain\ndoes not lag behind the skull"},{"time":667080,"text":"but instead it moves\nin synchrony with the skull,"},{"time":670680,"text":"then we might be able to prevent\nthis mechanism of concussion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":673960,"text":"So how can we slow the head down?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":678640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":680400,"text":"A gigantic helmet."},{"time":683440,"text":"So with more space, you have more time,"},{"time":686320,"text":"and this is a bit of a joke,\nbut some of you may have seen this."},{"time":689440,"text":"This is bubble soccer,\nand it's a real sport."},{"time":691760,"text":"In fact, I saw some young adults"},{"time":693440,"text":"playing this sport down the street\nfrom my house the other day,"},{"time":696440,"text":"and as far as I know\nthere have been no reported concussions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699360,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":700400,"text":"But in all seriousness,\nthis principle does work,"},{"time":704840,"text":"but this has gone too far."},{"time":706240,"text":"This isn't something that's practical\nfor bike riding or playing football."},{"time":711520,"text":"And so we are collaborating\nwith a company in Sweden called Hövding."},{"time":715920,"text":"Some of you may have seen their work,"},{"time":718280,"text":"and they're using the same principle\nof air to give you some extra space"},{"time":722680,"text":"to prevent concussion."},{"time":725320,"text":"Kids, don't try this at home please."},{"time":728680,"text":"This stuntman does not have a helmet."},{"time":732200,"text":"He instead has a neck collar,"},{"time":734480,"text":"and this neck collar has sensors in it,"},{"time":737080,"text":"the same type of sensors\nthat are in our mouthguard,"},{"time":740680,"text":"and it detects when he's likely\nto have a fall,"},{"time":743840,"text":"and there's an airbag\nthat explodes and triggers,"},{"time":746200,"text":"the same way that an airbag\nworks in your car, essentially."},{"time":750000,"text":"And in the experiments\nwe've done in my lab with their device,"},{"time":752960,"text":"we found that it can greatly reduce\nthe risk of concussion in some scenarios"},{"time":756720,"text":"compared to a normal bicycle helmet."},{"time":758880,"text":"So it's a pretty exciting development."}]},{"cues":[{"time":761720,"text":"But in order for us to actually realize\nthe benefits of technology"},{"time":766440,"text":"that can prevent concussion,"},{"time":768320,"text":"it needs to meet regulations."},{"time":771280,"text":"That's a reality."},{"time":773000,"text":"And this device is for sale in Europe"},{"time":776160,"text":"but is not for sale in the US,\nand probably won't be any time soon."},{"time":779880,"text":"So I wanted to tell you why."},{"time":781440,"text":"There are some good reasons and then\nthere are some not so good reasons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":785240,"text":"Bike helmets are federally regulated."},{"time":787480,"text":"The Consumer Product Safety Commission\nhas been given jurisdiction"},{"time":791240,"text":"to approve any bike helmet for sale,"},{"time":793120,"text":"and this is the test they use."},{"time":794600,"text":"This is back to what I was telling you\nat the beginning about skull fracture."},{"time":798280,"text":"That's what this test is for."},{"time":799720,"text":"And that's an important thing to do."},{"time":801480,"text":"It can save your life,\nbut it's not sufficient, I would say."},{"time":804360,"text":"So for example, one thing\nthis test doesn't evaluate"},{"time":807120,"text":"is it doesn't tell you\nis that airbag going to trigger"},{"time":809960,"text":"at the right time and place,\nand not trigger when it doesn't need to?"},{"time":813880,"text":"Similarly, it's not going to tell you"},{"time":815960,"text":"is this helmet likely\nto prevent concussion or not?"},{"time":819360,"text":"And if you look at football helmets,\nwhich aren't regulated,"},{"time":823120,"text":"they still have a very similar test."},{"time":825520,"text":"They're not regulated\nby the government, anyway."},{"time":827800,"text":"They have an industry body,\nwhich is the way most industries work."},{"time":830960,"text":"But this industry body, I can tell you,\nhas been quite resistant"},{"time":834000,"text":"to updating their standards."},{"time":835400,"text":"So in my lab, we are working on not only\nthe mechanism of concussion,"},{"time":838680,"text":"but we want to understand\nhow can we have better test standards?"},{"time":842160,"text":"And we hope that the government\ncan use this type of information"},{"time":846720,"text":"to encourage innovation"},{"time":848480,"text":"by letting consumers know"},{"time":850120,"text":"how protected are you with a given helmet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":853920,"text":"And I want to bring this back finally\nto the original question I asked,"},{"time":857320,"text":"which is, would I feel comfortable\nletting my child play football"},{"time":860680,"text":"or ride a bicycle?"},{"time":862440,"text":"And this might be just a result\nof my own traumatic experience."},{"time":865800,"text":"I'm much more nervous\nabout my daughter, Rose, riding a bicycle."},{"time":870920,"text":"So she's a year and a half old,"},{"time":872600,"text":"and she's already, well, wants to anyway,\nrace down the streets of San Francisco."},{"time":878080,"text":"This is the bottom\nof one of these streets."},{"time":880440,"text":"And so my personal goal\nis to -- and I believe this is possible --"},{"time":885680,"text":"is to further develop these technologies,"},{"time":887760,"text":"and in fact, we're working\non something in my lab in particular"},{"time":890760,"text":"that really makes optimal use\nof the given space of a helmet."},{"time":893737,"text":"And I am confident\nthat we will be able to,"},{"time":896240,"text":"before she's ready to ride a two-wheeler,"},{"time":899480,"text":"have something available"},{"time":900880,"text":"that can in fact really reduce\nthe risk of concussion"},{"time":904240,"text":"and comply with regulatory bodies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":907400,"text":"And so what I'd like to do --"},{"time":909040,"text":"and I know that this is for some of you\nof more immediate nature,"},{"time":912440,"text":"I've got a couple years here --"},{"time":914120,"text":"is to be able to tell parents\nand grandparents when I'm asked,"},{"time":918280,"text":"it is safe and healthy for your children\nto engage in these activities."},{"time":922720,"text":"And I'm very fortunate\nto have a wonderful team at Stanford"},{"time":925560,"text":"that's working hard on this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":927480,"text":"So I hope to come back in a few years\nwith the final story,"},{"time":931600,"text":"but for now I will tell you,"},{"time":933600,"text":"please don't just be afraid\nwhen you hear the word concussion."},{"time":936560,"text":"There is hope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":937800,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":939040,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}